  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AbstractModule
    The AbstractModule class represents modules/tools provided by the Module Taxonomy as well as their abstraction classes.
    AllModules
    The AllModules class represent the set of all modules/tools that can be part of our program.
    AllTypes
    The AllTypes class represent the set of all data types/formats that can be used in our program.
    AtomMapping
    Class is used to store the data used for representing the atoms with integer numbers.
    ConstraintData
    The {#code ConstraintData} class is used to store the data describing each constrain.
    Module
    The Module class represents concrete modules/tools that can be used in our program.
    Module_Execution_Code  
    Pair
    The Pair class represents pairs of objects, in our case used to store pairs of AbstractModules, Modules or Types.
    Type
    The Type class represents data type/format that can be used by our tools.
